import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['type'] = data['type'].astype('category')
    chart = sns.countplot(x='type', data=data)
    for p in chart.patches:
        chart.annotate(str(p.get_height()), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha='center', va='center', xytext=(0, 10), textcoords='offset points')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the type of deaths?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of the deaths?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
